msgid "Using the SurfaceTool"
msgstr "Ag baint úsáide as an SurfaceTool"

msgid ""
"The :ref:`SurfaceTool <class_surfacetool>` provides a useful interface for "
"constructing geometry. The interface is similar to the :ref:`ImmediateMesh "
"<class_ImmediateMesh>` class. You set each per-vertex attribute (e.g. "
"normal, uv, color) and then when you add a vertex it captures the attributes."
msgstr ""
"Soláthraíonn an :ref:`SurfaceTool <class_surfacetool>` comhéadan úsáideach "
"chun céimseata a thógáil. Tá an comhéadan cosúil leis an "
"rang :ref:`ImmediateMesh <class_ImmediateMesh>`. Socraíonn tú gach "
"aitreabúid in aghaidh an rinn (m.sh. gnáth, uv, dath) agus ansin nuair a "
"chuireann tú rinn leis gabhálann sé na tréithe."

msgid ""
"The SurfaceTool also provides some useful helper functions like ``index()`` "
"and ``generate_normals()``."
msgstr ""
"Soláthraíonn an SurfaceTool roinnt feidhmeanna cabhracha úsáideacha cosúil "
"le ''index()'' agus ''generate_normals()''."

msgid "Attributes are added before each vertex is added:"
msgstr "Cuirtear tréithe leis sula gcuirtear gach stuaic leis:"

msgid ""
"Similarly, if you have an index array, but you want each vertex to be unique "
"(e.g. because you want to use unique normals or colors per face instead of "
"per-vertex), you can call ``deindex()``."
msgstr ""
"Mar an gcéanna, má tá eagar innéacs agat, ach más mian leat go mbeadh gach "
"stuaic uathúil (m.sh. toisc gur mian leat gnáthaimh nó dathanna uathúla a "
"úsáid in aghaidh an duine in ionad per-vertex), is féidir leat ''deindex()' "
"a ghlaoch."

msgid ""
"If you don't add custom normals yourself, you can add them using "
"``generate_normals()``, which should be called after generating geometry and "
"before committing the mesh using ``commit()`` or ``commit_to_arrays()``. "
"Calling ``generate_normals(true)`` will flip the resulting normals. As a "
"side note, ``generate_normals()`` only works if the primitive type is set to "
"``Mesh.PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES``."
msgstr ""
"Mura gcuireann tú gnáthaimh shaincheaptha leat féin, is féidir leat iad a "
"chur leis ag baint úsáide as ''generate_normals()'', ar chóir iad a ghlaoch "
"tar éis geoiméadracht a ghiniúint agus sula ndéanann tú an mogall ag baint "
"úsáide as ''commit()'' nó ''commit_to_arrays()''. Má ghlaonn tú ar "
"''generate_normals(fíor)'' smeachfaidh sé na gnáthaimh a thagann as. Mar "
"nóta taoibh, ní oibríonn ''generate_normals()'' ach amháin má tá an cineál "
"primitive leagtha ar ''Mesh.PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES''."

msgid ""
"You may notice that normal mapping or other material properties look broken "
"on the generated mesh. This is because normal mapping **requires** the mesh "
"to feature *tangents*, which are separate from *normals*. You can either add "
"custom tangents manually, or generate them automatically with "
"``generate_tangents()``. This method requires that each vertex have UVs and "
"normals set already."
msgstr ""
"D'fhéadfá a thabhairt faoi deara go bhfuil cuma bhriste ar an mogall ginte "
"ar ghnáthmhapáil nó airíonna ábhartha eile. Tá sé seo amhlaidh toisc go n-"
"éilíonn gnáthmhapáil **** an mogall chun *tangents *a chur san áireamh, atá "
"scartha ó *normals *. Is féidir leat tadhlaí saincheaptha a chur leis de "
"láimh, nó iad a ghiniúint go huathoibríoch le ''generate_tangents()''. "
"Éilíonn an modh seo go bhfuil UVanna agus gnáthaimh socraithe cheana féin ag "
"gach stuaic."
